data.name: checkBoxUseAirportCode.ToolTip
data.value:
The FAA has numbered each Airport with a number. The files by default have this number instead of their name. Checking this box will change the number to its FAA Airport Code. eg. 00188 is MDT (Harrisburg Intl), it is shown at the top of the approach plate without the preceding 0's.
FAA condenses the approach names in the filenames eg. ILS Runway 31 = IL31, RNAV 26 = R26, VOR 31 = V31 This will instead use the full approach name. eg. ILS Runway 31 = ILS RWY 31, RNAV 26 = RNAV RWY 26
